 which all the events E</span><sub><span>1</span></sub><span>, E</span><sub=
><span>2</span></sub><span>,=E2=80=A6, E</span><sub><span>n</span></sub><sp=
an> have a non-zero probability of occurrence. All the events E</span><sub>=
<span>1</span></sub><span>, E</span><sub><span>2</span></sub><span>,=E2=80=
=A6, E form a partition of S. Let A be an event in space S for which we hav=
e to find the probability, then according to Bayes theorem,</span></p><bloc=
kquote><p dir=3D"ltr" style=3D"overflow: auto hidden; padding: 2px;"><gfg-t=
